2011;;The Music Never Stopped;;American;;Jim Kohlberg;;J. K. Simmons, Lou Taylor Pucci, Cara Seymour, Julia Ormond, Tammy Blanchard, MÃ­a Maestro, Scott Adsit, James Urbaniak;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Music_Never_Stopped;;Based on Oliver Sacks' essay The Last Hippie, the film tells the father-son relationship between Henry Sawyer (J.K. Simmons) and his son, Gabriel (Lou Taylor Pucci), who suffers from a brain tumor that prevents him from forming new memories. Henry, with his son unable to shed light on their strained relationship, must connect with him through music.